'''Waman Gopal Joshi''' ({{lang-mr|वामन गोपाळ जोशी}}) (18 March 1881 – 3 June 1956) was a [[Marathi people|Marathi]] journalist, playwright, and freedom fighter, from [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].<ref>{{Citation
  | last = National Informatics Center, Amravati District
  | title = The Land of Great Men
  | url = http://amravati.gov.in/htmldocs/great.htm
  | accessdate = 27 July 2011 }}
</ref>  He was the editor of Rashtramat and Swatantra Hindustan during the freedom struggle of India.  He courted arrest and came to be known as Veer Wamanrao Joshi or Veer Vamanrao Joshi. He wrote the play 'RaNa-dundubhi', whose songs were made famous by Dinanath Mangeshkar.

Waman Gopal Joshi should not be confused with the writer Vaman Malhar Joshi. They were contemporaries.

==Literary work==
* ''Rakshasi Mahattvakanksha'' (1914)
* ''Ranadundubhi'' (1927)

